prompt_template:
Create a {ASPECT_RATIO} image in the "red-yellow-product-trophy-collage-style" visual style.

Subject: {SUBJECT}
Action: {SUBJECT_ACTION}
Prop/Product: {PRODUCT_OR_PROP}
Location: {LOCATION}
Background: {BACKGROUND_ELEMENTS}
Main text: {MAIN_TEXT}
Secondary text: {SECONDARY_TEXT}
Accent symbol: {ACCENT_SYMBOL}
Wardrobe/styling: {WARDROBE_STYLE}
Style fidelity anchors: {STYLE_FIDELITY_ANCHORS}
Source content to avoid: {SOURCE_CONTENT_TO_AVOID}

Apply these style rules:
- Composition: build a central world-champion trophy silhouette from many small product objects; use a globe-like top, narrowed waist, flared base, and symmetrical upward side curves, with a big headline band above and a narrow footer strip below. Keep the background plain and graphic, not scenic.
- Typography: use massive condensed sans-serif headline type in white or yellow, tight grid alignment, small legal-like microcopy bars, and no official brand names or slogans.
- Color: use a saturated red field, warm yellow panels, white highlights, small green or black accents, and high commercial poster contrast.
- Texture and lighting: combine glossy studio product photography with flat poster shadows, crisp cutout edges, bright commercial highlights, and a clean print finish.
- Graphic elements: use rounded blocks, arch-like curves, sticker bursts, arrow tabs, star separators, and small price-panel-like rectangles, but no real logos.

Avoid: exact McDonald's, FIFA, Coca-Cola, Nike, Adidas, LEGO, Apple, Starbucks, or other official logos; no official trophy replica; no QR codes, no watermarks, no UI, no photoreal crowd scene, no mascot, no celebrity, no exact packaging trade dress.

Important content rule: match the fast-food billboard inspired layout first, then change the content by using the specified product family to construct an original trophy silhouette.
